Liverpool host Tottenham Hotspur in the Premier League game of the week this Sunday. The Reds currently top the table, despite seeing their 100% start to the season end at Manchester United last weekend. Spurs, who have endured a stop-start campaign, will be seeking to exact some form of revenge, having lost to Jurgen Klopp’s men in the Champions League final this year. Kick off is 5.30pm Liverpool XI: Alisson, Alexander-Arnold, Lovren, Van Dijk, Robertson, Fabinho, Henderson, Wijnaldum, Salah, Firmino, Mane Tottenham XI: Gazzaniga, Aurier, Alderweireld, Sanchez, Rose, Winks, Sissoko, Eriksen, Dele, Son, Kane Sunday, October 27
